Definition.WordDefinition: Clothespin \Clothes"pin`\ (? or ?), n. A forked piece of wood or plastic, or a small device with a spring clamp, used for fastening clothes on a line. [1913 Webster +PJC]
clothes pin n : wood or plastic fastener; for holding clothes on a clothesline [syn: {clothespin}, {clothes peg}]
clothespin n : wood or plastic fastener; for holding clothes on a clothesline [syn: {clothes pin}, {clothes peg}]
